@mipetriu done!

> If the resource accessed by your app's interactive request does not have the same CA requirement, those claims may not be requested.

Our app's interactive token request is supposed to trigger bundled consent — our server app's manifest lists our client app ID in its knownClientApplications array. The goal here is for the customer to auth & consent once and have it apply to both the client and the server. Shouldn't the bundled consent process also account for CA requirements for all resources that the apps will need?

